-{"id":"flywheel_gateway-1en","title":"Migrate from custom CSS to Tailwind CSS 4.0","description":"## Task
Migrate the 1927-line custom CSS file (apps/web/src/index.css) to Tailwind CSS 4.0 with design tokens and utility classes.

## Why This Matters
- Tailwind 4.0 (Jan 2025) offers 5x faster builds with native CSS cascade layers
- CSS-first configuration reduces complexity
- Consistent design tokens improve maintainability
- Per research: "Modern CSS features: @property support, container queries, wide-gamut colors"
- Currently using 1927 lines of custom CSS that duplicates what Tailwind provides

## Files to Modify/Create
1. apps/web/package.json (add tailwindcss)
2. apps/web/tailwind.config.ts (NEW)
3. apps/web/src/index.css (refactor to @tailwind directives + custom tokens)
4. apps/web/src/components/**/*.tsx (add utility classes)
5. apps/web/postcss.config.js (if needed for Vite)

## Current State Analysis
```css
/* apps/web/src/index.css - 1927 lines including: */

/* Lines 1-98: CSS Variables (colors, spacing, animations) */
:root {
  --color-bg: #ffffff;
  --color-text: #1a1a2e;
  /* ... 50+ more variables */
}

/* Lines 100-400: Base/Reset styles */
/* Lines 400-800: Component styles (.btn, .card, .modal, etc.) */
/* Lines 800-1200: Layout styles (.container, .grid, etc.) */
/* Lines 1200-1600: Page-specific styles */
/* Lines 1600-1927: Dark mode overrides, animations, utilities */
```

## Target State with Tailwind 4.0
```css
/* apps/web/src/index.css - ~200 lines */
@import "tailwindcss";

/* Custom design tokens using Tailwind 4 @theme directive */
@theme {
  /* Colors - mapped from existing CSS variables */
  --color-bg-primary: oklch(98% 0.01 250);
  --color-bg-secondary: oklch(96% 0.01 250);
  --color-text-primary: oklch(20% 0.02 260);
  --color-text-muted: oklch(50% 0.02 260);

  /* Status colors */
  --color-success: oklch(72% 0.2 145);
  --color-warning: oklch(80% 0.18 85);
  --color-error: oklch(65% 0.25 25);
  --color-info: oklch(70% 0.15 230);

  /* Spacing scale (preserve existing) */
  --spacing-xs: 0.25rem;
  --spacing-sm: 0.5rem;
  --spacing-md: 1rem;
  --spacing-lg: 1.5rem;
  --spacing-xl: 2rem;

  /* Animation durations */
  --duration-fast: 150ms;
  --duration-normal: 300ms;
  --duration-slow: 500ms;

  /* Border radius */
  --radius-sm: 0.25rem;
  --radius-md: 0.5rem;
  --radius-lg: 1rem;
}

/* Dark mode using native CSS */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  @theme {
    --color-bg-primary: oklch(15% 0.02 260);
    --color-bg-secondary: oklch(20% 0.02 260);
    --color-text-primary: oklch(95% 0.01 250);
  }
}

/* Manual theme override */
[data-theme="dusk"] {
  @theme {
    --color-bg-primary: oklch(15% 0.02 260);
    /* ... dark overrides */
  }
}

/* Component base layers (only for things Tailwind can't do) */
@layer base {
  body {
    @apply bg-bg-primary text-text-primary font-sans antialiased;
  }
}

/* Custom component classes (minimize these) */
@layer components {
  .btn {
    @apply px-4 py-2 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors duration-fast;
  }
  .btn--primary {
    @apply bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700;
  }
  /* Only ~20-30 component classes needed */
}
```

## Migration Strategy (Incremental)

### Phase 1: Setup & Tokens (~2 hours)
1. Install Tailwind 4.0 and configure
2. Extract all CSS variables into @theme
3. Keep existing CSS working alongside Tailwind

### Phase 2: Component Migration (~4 hours)
1. Migrate buttons (.btn-*) to Tailwind utilities
2. Migrate cards (.card-*) to Tailwind utilities
3. Migrate forms (.input-*, .select-*) to Tailwind utilities
4. Migrate modals (.modal-*) to Tailwind utilities

### Phase 3: Layout Migration (~2 hours)
1. Migrate grid system to Tailwind grid
2. Migrate container/wrapper classes
3. Migrate responsive breakpoints

### Phase 4: Cleanup (~2 hours)
1. Remove unused CSS
2. Consolidate remaining custom styles
3. Document token system
4. Final size optimization

## Component Migration Examples

### Before (Custom CSS)
```tsx
// Button.tsx
<button className="btn btn--primary btn--lg">
  Click me
</button>

// index.css
.btn { padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; }
.btn--primary { background: var(--color-primary); color: white; }
.btn--lg { padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; font-size: 1.125rem; }
```

### After (Tailwind 4.0)
```tsx
// Button.tsx - using utilities directly
<button className="px-6 py-3 text-lg bg-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg 
                   hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors">
  Click me
</button>

// OR using component class (for complex/repeated patterns)
<button className="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
  Click me
</button>

// With minimal component CSS:
@layer components {
  .btn-primary { @apply bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700; }
  .btn-lg { @apply px-6 py-3 text-lg; }
}
```

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests (apps/web/src/__tests__/styles/)
```typescript
// tailwind-tokens.test.ts
describe("Tailwind Design Tokens", () => {
  it("should have all required color tokens", () => {
    const root = document.documentElement;
    const styles = getComputedStyle(root);

    const requiredColors = [
      "--color-bg-primary",
      "--color-bg-secondary", 
      "--color-text-primary",
      "--color-text-muted",
      "--color-success",
      "--color-warning",
      "--color-error",
      "--color-info",
    ];

    requiredColors.forEach(color => {
      expect(styles.getPropertyValue(color)).not.toBe("");
    });
  });

  it("should have all spacing tokens", () => {
    const spacings = ["xs", "sm", "md", "lg", "xl"];
    spacings.forEach(size => {
      expect(getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
        .getPropertyValue(`--spacing-${size}`)).not.toBe("");
    });
  });
});

// component-styles.test.tsx
describe("Component Styling", () => {
  it("button should have correct styles", () => {
    render(<Button variant="primary">Test</Button>);
    const button = screen.getByRole("button");
    const styles = getComputedStyle(button);

    expect(styles.backgroundColor).toBe("rgb(37, 99, 235)"); // blue-600
    expect(styles.borderRadius).toBe("8px"); // rounded-lg
  });

  it("card should have correct padding and shadow", () => {
    render(<Card>Content</Card>);
    const card = screen.getByTestId("card");
    const styles = getComputedStyle(card);

    expect(styles.padding).toBe("16px"); // p-4
    expect(styles.boxShadow).not.toBe("none");
  });

  it("dark mode should apply correct colors", () => {
    document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-theme", "dusk");
    render(<Card>Content</Card>);
    const card = screen.getByTestId("card");
    const styles = getComputedStyle(card);

    // Dark mode background should be darker
    expect(styles.backgroundColor).toMatch(/rgb\(\d+, \d+, \d+\)/);
  });
});
